Cubic Learning Diary – Step-by-Step Notes
1. Install Programming & Productivity Tools

Install programming languages you need.

Install a terminal and terminal helper tools.

Install productivity tools like VS Code.

Use references like Omarchy for guidance.

2. Legal OS Customization

Edit /etc/lsb-release to set OS=release for legal distribution.

3. Customize Boot & Plymouth

Change the Plymouth boot image (Ubuntu default).

Modify background images and spinner in Plymouth themes XML files.

4. Enable File Extensions

Install required libraries for extensions, e.g., glib, gio, and code.

For Arc Menu, edit the GNOME extension folder, then recompile.

5. Desktop Icons

Install custom icons in /usr/share/icons/hicolor/48x48/apps.

Add .desktop files to /etc/skel/Desktop to ensure they appear for new users.

Apply execution permissions:

chmod +x /etc/skel/Desktop/*.desktop


Make sure desktop icons are read-only for other users but executable.

6. Terminal Customization

Remove the default Ubuntu terminal.

Install Alacritty and set its .desktop name as "Terminal".

Ensure it auto-reinstalls if removed during upgrades.

7. Snap & Flatpak

Remove Snap and Flatpak to reduce OS size.

Install Firefox via another method to ensure a browser is available.

8. GNOME Extensions

Remove preinstalled window system extensions like monitor light styles.

Remove default app menus and unnecessary GNOME extensions.

9. Custom-root Access

Use terminal to give your user full root access in custom-root.

Ensure you can copy/edit all necessary system files.

10. Zsh, Oh My Zsh, Powerlevel10k, LazyVim

Configure /etc/skel to include:

Zsh

Oh My Zsh

Powerlevel10k

LazyVim

Optionally, set Zsh as default shell for new users:

sed -i 's|^SHELL=.*|SHELL=/usr/bin/zsh|' /etc/default/useradd

11. Grub & Boot Fixes

Upgrade Grub in Cubic’s source-root to fix boot images.

Edit necessary Grub files; do not rely on sudo nvim alone.

Install Grub manually if required from GitHub tar files and update $PATH.

12. Arc Menu Customization

Edit Arc Menu to add your custom menu items.

Remove the default Ubuntu menu entries.

13. Multimedia & Commands

Install missing software:

VLC

bat command

Other essential command-line tools

14. Cubic Environment

After customizing Cubic virtual environment:

Remove --quirk or pslash options to fix boot loading.

